code: According to Article 10 of the Law on Lobbying, the Secretary General of the Assembly of the Republic of Macedonia keeps a Registry of Lobbyists, and the Registry is available to the public.

code: According to Article 21 of the Law on Prevention of Corruption, MPs are not allowed to be members of the management board in a privately owned company. According to Article 8 of the Electoral Code and Article 21 of the Law on Prevention of Corruption, MPs are not allowed to be members of the management board in a publicly owned company.
text: De acuerdo con el artículo 21 de la Ley de la prevención de corrupción, los miembros del parlamento no pueden ser miembros de los comités administrativos en las empresas privadas. De acuerdo con el Artículo 8 del Código Electoral y el artículo 21 de la Ley de la prevención de corrupción, los miembros del parlamento no pueden ser miembros de los comités en las empresas públicas.

code: According to law, a report on the Knesset expenditures is submitted to a joined committee headed by the Knesset Speaker. The protocol of the committee is on the internet. See example from 2013 -   http://www.knesset.gov.il/protocols/data/rtf/knesset/2014-07-28.rtf
text: De acuerdo con la ley, el informe sobre los gastos de Knesset esta presentado a un comité conjunto por el presidente de Knesset. El protocolo del comité está disponible en internet. Por ejemplo del año 2013 -   http://www.knesset.gov.il/protocols/data/rtf/knesset/2014-07-28.rtf

code: According to the Freedom of Information Law every citizen has the right to receive information from a public authority.

code: According to the Law on Lobbying, registry lists of active lobbyists are public.
text: De acuerdo con la Ley de Lobby, las listas de los miembros de lobbys son públicas.

code: According to the Law on prevention of conflict of interests, public official including MPs may not be the president or member of a management body nor supervisory body,  executive director, member of management of the public company, public institution or other legal entity.
text: De acuerdo con la Ley de prevención del conflicto de los interéses, los funcionarios públicos, incluyendo a los miembros del parlamento, no pueden ser miembros de los comités de supervisión ni de los comités de administración, directores ejecutivos, miembros de la administración de las empresas públicas, instituciones públicas u otras entidades legales.

code: This is a very complex area!  Oral and written evidence to Committees is published on the Committee's pages: e.g. http://www.parliament.uk/business/committees/committees-a-z/commons-select/home-affairs-committee/publications.  Command Papers are the collective name given to different types of papers prepared by the Government and presented to Parliament with the words "presented to Parliament by command of His/Her Majesty". The following documents are all types of Command Paper: Treaties, some White papers, some Green Papers, some Government replies to Select Committee reports, reports of Royal Commissions, reports of some major committees of inquiry, annual reports and statistics of certain bodies (judicial, penal, immigration).  These are published by Government rather than Parliament: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications and use "official document status" filter on LH side of page.  Also available for public inspection in Parliament.  For further info see http://www.parliament.uk/about/how/publications/government/
